  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site supervisor",
  "description": "<p><p><p><strong>Job Scope</strong><br /><br />Supervise day-to-day site operations for renovation works.</p><p>Ensure work is carried out according to drawings, specifications, and schedules.</p><p>Coordinate and monitor subcontractors, workers, and suppliers.</p><p>Assign tasks and ensure productivity on-site.</p><p>Inspect workmanship and materials to meet required standards.</p><p>Report and rectify defects or non-compliance issues promptly.</p><p>Enforce workplace safety regulations and ensure PPE usage.</p><p>Conduct toolbox meetings and safety briefings.</p><p>Ensure compliance with local building codes and regulations.</p><p>Prepare daily site reports, including work progress, manpower, and issues.</p></p><ul><li>Liaise with consultants, architects, and engineers for technical clarifications.</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain site records (attendance, material delivery, inspection reports).</li><li>Track material usage and request replenishment when needed.</li><li>Assist in preparing documentation for inspections and approvals.</li></ul><p>🔹 Skills & Competencies</p><ul><li>Strong leadership and communication skills.</li><li>Knowledge of construction methods, materials, and safety standards.</li><li>Ability to read and interpret technical drawings.</li><li>Problem-solving and decision-making under pressure.</li></ul></p>",
